HEADWORD: Tyrannicide
<hw>Ty*ran"ni*ci`de</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tyrannicidium</ets> the killing of a tyrant, <ets>tyrannicida</ets>
the killer of a tyrant; <ets>tyrannus</ets> a tyrant +
<ets>caedere</ets> to kill: cf. F. <ets>tyrannicide</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of killing a tyrant.</def>
<rj><au>Hume.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who kills a tyrant.</def>⟦br⟧
